- Sentence A: "When you smile at others, they will smile at you"
- Sentence B: "When you smile at others, they will cry to you"
column3: Smiling conveys happiness to other people, and happiness is often reciprocated.

Choose the sentence that goes against common sense.
Options:
- Sentence A: "Max stays close to the campfire to keep cool"
- Sentence B: "Max stays close to the campfire to keep warm"
column3: Being close to a campfire would make you warm because fire is hot.

Pick which sentence is not logical.
Options:
- Sentence A: "I have a desk on my lamp"
- Sentence B: "I have a lamp on my desk"
column3: A desk would most likely crush a lamp.
